{"word":"Βρόμιος","slug":"Βρόμιος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>Βρόμιος</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>from <a href='S:βρόμιος'><el>βρόμιος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b>as a name of Bacchus, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; <el>Βρομίου πῶμα</el>, <a href='S:id est'>i. e.</a> wine, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>as <a href='S:Adjective'>adj.</a> <el>Βρόμιος, α, ον</el>, <i>Bacchic</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}